1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 70 of Title 62, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The State Treasurer or a third-party vendor contracted by
5 the Office of the State Treasurer shall be authorized to issue a
6 transaction card to United States citizens with the ability to make
7 purchases that are debited from the balance of deposits with a
8 bullion depository created by the Office of the State Treasurer or
9 contracted with other public or private entities operating a bullion
10 depository.
11 B. Upon the creation of a depository or a contractual agreement
12 with an entity pursuant to subsection A of this section, the Office
13 of the State Treasurer shall:
14 1. Provide procedures for the sharing of account information
15 between the depository and the State Treasurer upon consent of the
16 account holder; and
17 2. Develop a fee structure for both the depository and the
18 Treasurer, to be paid by the account holder, to utilize the service
19 provided by a bullion depository.
20 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 70.1 of Title 62, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. Deposits of gold and silver in the bullion depository and
24 transactions made using the transaction card issued by the State
