1 Trea surer shall be considered legal tender, pursuant to the
2 authority vested upon this state in Section 10 of Article I of the
3 United States Constitution. Deposits of gold and silver in the
4 bullion depository shall not be considered a commodity. The
5 transfer, buying, or selling of gold and silver held in the
6 depository for transactions shall not be considered an exchange of a
7 commodity, and shall be considered an exchange of currency.
8 B. Account holders issued a transaction card may make
9 transactions debited against the value of gold and silver deposits
10 in the bullion depository.
11 C. The Treasurer may promulgate rules to implement the
12 provisions of this act.
13 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
